{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πυνθάνομαι</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.315, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>poetry</i> also <b>πεύθομαι</b> (which see): <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> πυνθανόμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 13.256 \">Refs</a>]: <i>future</i> πεύσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.19, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <i>Doric dialect</i> πευσοῦμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 3.51 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] (so codex <i>middle</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 988)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐπῠθόμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5. 702 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], etc., <i>Epic dialect</i> and Lyric poetry πυθόμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.732, 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 15.26 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>imperative</i> πυθοῦ, <i>Ionic dialect</i> πυθεῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>optative</i> πεπύθοιτο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.50, +others (_subjunctive_ πεπύθωνται is _falsa lectio_ for{γε πύθωνται}, 7.195)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> πυθοίατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 921 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> πέπυσμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.505, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>2nd pers.</i> <i>singular</i> πέπῠσαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 310b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Epic dialect</i> πέπυσσαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.494 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>infinitive</i> πεπύσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.67, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>participle</i> πεπυσμένος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 179e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>pluperfect</i> ἐπεπύσμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 615, “Av.” 470 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> ἐπέπυστο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.674, _Epic dialect_ πέπυστο [prev. work] 521 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>dual</i> πεπύσθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 17.377 \">Refs</a>]:—<b>learn</b>, whether <b>by hearsay</b> or <b>by inquiry</b> (ἐξιστορήσαντες τὰ ἐβούλοντο πυθέσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.195): _construction_ \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> π. τί τινος <b>learn</b> something <b>from</b> a person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.408, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.537, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 599, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1417, etc.; also π. τι ἀπό τινος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 737; ἐξ ἄλλων 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1266; ἐκ τοῦ παρατυχόντος 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.22 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; frequently παρά τινος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.91, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; παρ᾽ ἄλλων (variant{ἄλλων}) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.1.3. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i> only, <b>hear</b> or <b>learn</b> a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.411, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 765, 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.25, etc.: _absolutely_, αἰσχρὸν τόδε γ᾽ ἐστὶ καὶ ἐσσομένοισι πυθέσθαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.119, compare 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 7.7, etc.; ὡς ἐγὼ πυνθάνομαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.22, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i> objecti, <b>hear</b> or <b>inquire concerning</b>, πυθέσθαι πατρός, ἀγγελιάων, μάχης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.281, 2.256, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.224, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 35, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 635b. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> π. τινά τινος <b>inquire about</b> one person <b>of</b> or <b>from</b> another, τὸν ἄνδρα τῶν ὁδοιπόρων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 204; so π. περί τινος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.75; πᾶσαν πυθέσθαι τῶνδ᾽ ἀλήθειαν πέρι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 91 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i> only, <b>inquire about</b> a person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 619. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> with <i>participle</i>, πυθόμην ὁδὸν ὁρμαίνοντα that he was starting, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.732, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.58, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 692; π. τὸ Πλημμύριον ἑαλωκός 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.31, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.7.16, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οὔ πω.. πεπύσθην Πατρόκλοιο θανόντος they <b>had</b> not yet <b>heard of</b> his being dead, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.377, compare 427, 19.322, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 763; ὡς ἐπύθοντο τῆς Πύλου κατειλημμένης 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.6: with _accusative_ _of things_ added, εἰ σφῶϊν τάδε πάντα πυθοίατο μαρναμένοιιν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.257. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, <b>hear</b> or <b>learn that.. </b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.62, 5.15, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 103 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.25, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> followed by an <i>interrogative</i> clause, ὡς πυθώμεθα ὅπου ποτ᾽ ἐσμέν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αὐτοῦ π. τί ποτε νοεῖ <b>inquire</b> or <b>learn</b> from him what.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 196c, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 6.3.25, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.107.6; π., ὅτεῳ.. συνοικέει 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. εἰ.. <b>inquire</b> whether.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 993, “IG” 42(1).121.18 (Epid., 4th c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῦ ξένου ἡδέως ἂν π., τί ταῦθ᾽ ἡγοῦντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 216d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. τινῶν, ὅτι.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.6.17 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π., ὅπως ἂν κάλλιστα πορευθείη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 3.1.7, compare “Cyr.” 1.4.7. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>active</i>, <i>aorist 1</i> <i>participle</i> <i>feminine</i> πεύσασα <b>having learned,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PMasp. 5.7 (6th c.AD). \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]